### Employee CRUD Operations Test File
### Use this file to test the Employee API endpoints

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Get all employees (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/employees?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 2. Search employees by name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/employees/search?searchTerm=john
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 3. Search employees by department
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/employees/search?department=IT
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 4. Search with combined filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/employees/search?searchTerm=engineer&department=IT&pageSize=20
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 5. Get employee by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/employees/1
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 6. Check if employee exists
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/employees/1/exists
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 7. Create new employee
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/employees
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "department": "IT",
  "position": "Software Engineer",
  "hireDate": "2024-02-01T00:00:00Z"
}

### 8. Create another employee
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/employees
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+9876543210",
  "department": "HR",
  "position": "HR Manager",
  "hireDate": "2024-01-15T00:00:00Z"
